        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently the response body is stored as a string inside the response object. When it concerns big responses, like file downloads, this can take up quite some memory and you might go over PHP's memory limit.\n\nTo avoid such situations it would be nice to be able to write the body (after processing the transfer-encoding, NOT the raw body) directly into a PHP stream \/ file."
        },
